### BUILD-vs-DEFER premise check (P2 — the secrets tension)
The dev STAGE runners (`claude -p` etc.) and the model GATE SEATS (opus/codex/gemini) both
need credentials. Scoped secret passthrough is **etude-3a2 (NOT done)**; live runners get the
hermetic 3-var env (PATH, ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR, ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE) and CANNOT authenticate
(verified in internal/liverun/gate.go:113 and engine env). So a full real-LLM end-to-end
run is impossible today. **Committed scope** (matches the bead's sanctioned menu):
- BUILD now: the migrated `registry.yaml` + `workflow.yaml` PARSE+VALIDATE+fully cross-resolve
  under registry.ParseYAML / workflow.ParseYAML (no secrets); and `etude run` WALKS a graph
  live with deterministic runners while a DETERMINISTIC gate CHECK executes for real
  (checks need no secrets) — proving orchestration + gate execution end-to-end.
- DEFER (post-3a2, noted not faked): real-LLM execution of the actual dev stage runners and
  model-seat gate panels. AC1/AC2 are honestly satisfied at the orchestration + config/
  resolution + deterministic-check level; real-LLM seat EXECUTION waits on 3a2. This deferral
  is EXPLICITLY TRACKED in filed follow-up bead **etude-s6z** ("Drive the real dev workflow
  live end-to-end with real-LLM runners + model-seat gates", depends on etude-2pc.2 + etude-3a2)
  — not just a prose note.

